Amidst the rage of the Olympic Games, the Zen of the trampoline
Wherever you are, whatever it is, it's the Olympics.
The events in Rio de Janeiro feel constant and inevitable, a raging relay race between competition and aspiration.
It is as if the Olympic torch itself were a burning staff, which is served by the crossbow shooter to the swimmer to the gymnast to the triathlete.
